/*
========================================================
finish() IN ANDROID - COMPLETE NOTES
========================================================

WHAT IS finish() ?
--------------------------------------------------------
• finish() is a method of Activity class
• It closes the current Activity
• Removes the Activity from the back stack
• Returns control to the previous Activity

--------------------------------------------------------
WHY finish() IS USED ?
--------------------------------------------------------
• To close an Activity when its job is done
• To return to previous Activity
• To send result back to calling Activity
• To prevent multiple instances of Activity
• To control navigation flow

--------------------------------------------------------
finish() IN ACTIVITY RESULT SCENARIO
--------------------------------------------------------
• setResult() alone is NOT enough
• Result is delivered ONLY when Activity finishes
• finish() triggers the result callback in caller

Example:
setResult(RESULT_OK, intent)
finish()   // <-- mandatory

--------------------------------------------------------
WHAT HAPPENS INTERNALLY ?
--------------------------------------------------------
1. Activity lifecycle enters onPause()
2. Then onStop()
3. Then onDestroy()
4. Activity is removed from back stack
5. Previous Activity resumes
6. Result is delivered (if setResult was called)

--------------------------------------------------------
WHAT IF finish() IS NOT USED ?
--------------------------------------------------------
• Current Activity remains open
• Back stack is NOT cleared
• Caller Activity does NOT receive result
• Activity Result callback is NOT triggered
• User must press back manually

--------------------------------------------------------
finish() vs BACK BUTTON
--------------------------------------------------------
• Back button → System calls finish()
• finish() → App calls finish()

Both result in Activity closure

--------------------------------------------------------
WHEN TO USE finish() ?
--------------------------------------------------------
• After submitting a form
• After login success
• After returning result
• After splash screen
• When Activity should not stay in back stack

--------------------------------------------------------
WHEN NOT TO USE finish() ?
--------------------------------------------------------
• When user may return to Activity
• When temporary pause is needed
• When Activity state should persist

--------------------------------------------------------
COMMON INTERVIEW QUESTIONS
--------------------------------------------------------
Q: Is finish() mandatory for returning result?
A: YES

Q: Does finish() destroy activity?
A: YES

Q: Can finish() be called inside onCreate()?
A: YES (for splash screens)

--------------------------------------------------------
ONE-LINE SUMMARY
--------------------------------------------------------
finish() closes the current Activity and is required
to deliver results and manage navigation properly.
========================================================
*/
